Sophia1, 

The first thing I did was to [b:1n87kxu2]ADD [/b:1n87kxu2]the [i:1n87kxu2]integer [/i:1n87kxu2]variables in the [b:1n87kxu2]game.attributes[/b:1n87kxu2] TAB section:

sectorX = 0, sectorY = 0

Plus [b:1n87kxu2]ADD[/b:1n87kxu2]ing the variables for the x and y coords. for each island:

neosx = 0, neosy = 0, chanrax = 0, chanray = 0, etc.

Then in the [b:1n87kxu2]Script [/b:1n87kxu2]tab of [b:1n87kxu2]game [/b:1n87kxu2]a Call Function called [b:1n87kxu2]randoms[/b:1n87kxu2] was made to randomly create all the islands x and y coords.

This is the Call Function contents for [b:1n87kxu2]randoms[/b:1n87kxu2] (in part):

[b:1n87kxu2]Return type:[/b:1n87kxu2] None

[b:1n87kxu2]Parameters:[/b:1n87kxu2] &lt;LEAVE BLANK&gt;

[code:1n87kxu2]game&#46;neosx = GetRandomInt(100,199)
game&#46;neosy = GetRandomInt(100,199)
game&#46;chanrax = GetRandomInt(200,299)
game&#46;chanray = GetRandomInt(200,299)[/code:1n87kxu2]
Etc, plus many more random x and y variables…
 
Then in the [b:1n87kxu2]USE (on its own)[/b:1n87kxu2] section of the [b:1n87kxu2]flying craft[/b:1n87kxu2] object it asks for the X and Y coords:

[code:1n87kxu2]msg (&quot;Enter the Sector X co-ordinate?&quot;)
get input {
  if (IsInt (result)) {
    sectorX = ToInt (result)
    wait {
      msg (&quot;Enter the Sector Y co-ordinate?&quot;)
      get input {
        if (IsInt (result)) {
          sectorY = ToInt (result)
          sectorchecks (sectorX, sectorY)
        }
        else {
          msg (&quot;You need to enter a number&#46; Try USE CRAFT again&#46;&quot;)
        }
      }
    }
  }
  else {
    msg (&quot;You need to enter a number&#46; Try USE CRAFT again&#46;&quot;)
  }
}[/code:1n87kxu2]

This checks your input to the [b:1n87kxu2]Call Function[/b:1n87kxu2] named [b:1n87kxu2]sectorchecks[/b:1n87kxu2] which has two parameters you need to [b:1n87kxu2]ADD[/b:1n87kxu2]: 

sectorX 
sectorY

[b:1n87kxu2]Call Function [i:1n87kxu2]sectorchecks[/i:1n87kxu2][/b:1n87kxu2] contains:

Return type: Integer

Parameters:
sectorX
sectorY

[code:1n87kxu2]if (sectorX = game&#46;neosx) {
  if (sectorY = game&#46;neosy) {
    if (not game&#46;pov&#46;parent = landing platform 1) {
      msg (&quot;&lt;br/&gt;You fly off to your destination&#46;&quot;)
      MoveObject (flying craft, landing platform 1)
      MoveObject (player, landing platform 1)
    }
    else {
      msg (&quot;You are already at these co-ordinates&#46;&quot;)
    }
  }
  else {
    msg (&quot;They are not valid co-ordinates&#46; You're going nowhere&#46;&quot;)
  }
}
else if (sectorX = game&#46;chanrax) {
